    h2 Disabled Buttons
    p Buttons can be disabled by adding the <code>disabled</code> attribute.
    .code-example
      .code-output
        // Default Button
        a.button.mr-small(href='#', disabled) Default Button
        // Primary Button
        a.button.button-primary.mr-small(href='#', disabled) Primary Button
        // Light Button
        a.button.button-light.mr-small(href='#', disabled) Light Button
        // Ghost Button
        button.button.button-ghost.mr-small(disabled) Ghost Button
        // Text Button
        input.button.button-text.mr-small(type='submit', value='Text Button', disabled)
      pre
        code.
          #{'<!-- Disabled Buttons -->'}
          #{'<a class="button" href="#" disabled>Default Button</a>'}
          #{'<a class="button button-primary" href="#" disabled>Primary Button</a>'}
          #{'<a class="button button-light" href="#" disabled>Light Button</a>'}
          #{'<button class="button-ghost" disabled>Ghost Button</button>'}
          #{'<input class="button button-text" value="Text Button"  type="submit" disabled/>'}
    h2 Button Sizes
    p To change the button size, simply add the text size modifiers <code>text-small</code>, <code>text-medium</code> and <code>text-large</code> as shown below.
    .code-example
      .code-output
        a.button.button-primary.text-small.mr-small(href="#") Small Button
        a.button.button-primary.mr-small(href="#") Normal Button
        a.button.button-primary.text-large.mr-small(href="#") Large Button
      pre
        code.
          #{'<a class="button button-primary text-small" href="#">Small Button</a>'}
          #{'<a class="button button-primary" href="#">Normal Button</a>'}
          #{'<a class="button button-primary text-large" href="#">Large Button</a>'}
    h2 Block Button
    p Use <code>d-block</code> display utility class to create a block button style.
    .code-example
      .code-output
        a.button.button-primary.d-block(href="#") Block Button
        .grid.gutters
          .col
            a.button.d-block(href="#") Block Button
          .col
            a.button.d-block(href="#") Block Button
    pre
        code.
          #{'<a class="button button-primary d-block" href="#">Block Button</a>'}
          #{'<div class="grid gutters">'}
          #{' <div class="col"><a class="button d-block" href="#">Block Button</a></div>'}
          #{' <div class="col"><a class="button d-block" href="#">Block Button</a></div>'}
          #{'</div>'}

